performer.name: Hozier
performer.bio: Hozier, born Andrew Hozier-Byrne in 1990, is an Irish singer-songwriter known for his powerful voice and emotive lyrics. He rose to international fame with the release of his debut single "Take Me to Church" in 2013, which critiques societal norms and celebrates love and identity. Hozier's music blends elements of folk, blues, and rock, drawing influence from various genres and cultural backgrounds. His debut album, released in 2014, was critically acclaimed and showcased his talent for storytelling through song. Hozier's sophomore album, "Wasteland, Baby!" debuted at number one on the Billboard 200 in 2019, further establishing his place in contemporary music.
